# WXT Browser Extension Patterns

## Entry Points
WXT uses file-based routing for extension entry points:
- `entrypoints/background.ts` - Service worker
- `entrypoints/popup/` - Popup UI (index.html + React)
- `entrypoints/*.content.ts` - Content scripts
- `entrypoints/*-mainworld.ts` - Main world scripts

## Content Script Patterns
- Use `x-*.content.ts` naming for X/Twitter specific scripts
- Inject main world scripts using `x-mainworld.ts` pattern
- Handle DOM manipulation and message passing between contexts

## Configuration
- [wxt.config.ts](mdc:wxt.config.ts) defines build settings
- Use `@wxt-dev/module-react` for React integration
- Configure permissions in manifest object
- Set up web_accessible_resources for injected scripts

## Development
- `bun run dev` for development with hot reload
- `bun run build` for production builds
- Use Helium browser for testing (configured in wxt.config.ts)